Page 2: Methods, Formats, and Benefits
Communication and Methods:
The REST API serves as the core foundation for transferring data between the client/browser and the server.
When a client sends a request to an endpoint, the server responds with relevant information (e.g., user data).
HTTP Methods used in REST: GET, POST, PUT, PATCH, and DELETE.
Example: GET /api/user is a request from the client to the server for user information.
JSON (JavaScript Object Notation): This is the most common data format for REST APIs because it is lightweight and easy to use.
RESTful Webserver: A web server that uses REST APIs for communication.
Benefits of REST APIs:
Simple and Standard.
Scalable and Stateless.
High Performance.
Supports Caching.

