Page 3: CRUD Mapping and Statelessness
CRUD Mapping to HTTP Methods: REST APIs map standard database operations (CRUD) to specific HTTP methods:
C - Create: POST.
R - Read: GET.
U - Update: PUT, PATCH.
D - Delete: DELETE.
Status Codes: The server uses status codes to communicate the result of a request:
200: Successful.
201: Created.
204: Accidental sent (No Content).
400: Client mistake.
401: Unauthorized access.
403: Forbidden entry.
404: Page/Resource Not Found.
429: Too many requests.
500: Internal server error.
Stateless Architecture:
Statelessness means that in a REST architecture, each request from the client must contain all the information needed for the server to process it.
The server does not store session information between separate requests.